<taxonomicName authority="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra, 2020" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" box="[750,994,1816,1842]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalciope" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[750,994,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Schausiana chalciope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[999,1087,1816,1843]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[999,1025,1816,1842]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1082,1816,1842]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
), and (iii) the absence of black/ brown markings on the wing margin of the FW and (iv) the absence of black/brown markings at the intersection of the A and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[317,325,1906,1920]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">2</subScript>
veins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1563,1987]" box="[199,597,1924,1951]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,365,1924,1950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[380,441,1924,1950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[455,540,1924,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,211,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Schausiana phalerus. 12, ♂ HT: 12a, dorsal view; 12b, ventral view (NHMUK). 13, ♀ (CGCM 24.122): 13a, dorsal view; 13b, ventral view (CGCM). Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413516/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Figs 12</figureCitation>
a–b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1563,1987]" box="[199,677,1960,1987]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Head</emphasis>
. Frons ochrish-brown, vertex darker.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413516" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4413516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413516/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" startId="9.[151,264,1782,1806]" targetBox="[162,1425,211,1724]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1782,1842]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,333,1782,1806]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">FIGURES 12–13</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[344,555,1782,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis box="[344,555,1782,1806]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[566,591,1782,1806]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">12</emphasis>
, ♂ HT: 12a, dorsal view; 12b, ventral view (NHMUK). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1178,1782,1806]" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">13</emphasis>
, ♀ (CGCM 24.122): 13a, dorsal view; 13b, ventral view (CGCM). Scale bar = 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1888,2023]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="76">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pro- and mesothorax slightly lighter than vertex, metathorax greyish-brown, ventrally ochrish-brown, metathorax pale yellow. FW length: 
<quantity box="[558,680,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.75" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="57.5" valueMax="63.0" valueMin="52.0">52–63 mm</quantity>
, width: 
<quantity box="[770,890,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="21.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="20.0">20–23 mm</quantity>
(ratio ~2.7), wingspan: 
<quantity box="[1159,1309,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.215" metricValueMax="1.33" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="121.5" valueMax="133.0" valueMin="110.0">110–133 mm</quantity>
; elongated, tornus indistinct; costal margin slightly convex, apex pronounced and acute, outer margin slightly concave from apex to Rs3, inner margin convex. DFW ground colour ochrish-brown with numerous indistinct, transverse thin, dark brown stripes and dots over entire surface; anal area with a single detached black spot; U-shaped band brown, darker posteriorly, not reaching A vein, the proximal arm with a conspicuous silver irregular spot concolorous with the silver and oblique stigma; premarginal and marginal bands barely visible, slightly darker than ground colour; evenly spaced white spine-like specialized scales on the veins. DHW ground colour greyish-brown, costal margin distally brown with some darker spots. VFW and VHW greyish-brown with apex and veins distally dark yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[199,305,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Abdomen</emphasis>
. First two segments dorsally and ventrally concolorous with metathorax, segments III to VIII dorsally black with some dark blue reflecting scales, lighter posteriorly on each segment, ventrally pale yellow as the metathorax.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1034,439,466]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[199,364,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Not dissected (male 
<typeStatus box="[607,705,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[759,866,439,465]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">paratypes</typeStatus>
not available).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,595,474,502]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,474,500]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,439,475,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[454,537,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,211,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Schausiana phalerus. 12, ♂ HT: 12a, dorsal view; 12b, ventral view (NHMUK). 13, ♀ (CGCM 24.122): 13a, dorsal view; 13b, ventral view (CGCM). Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413516/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Figs 13</figureCitation>
a–b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,630,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[199,260,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Head</emphasis>
. Antenna with ~30 antenomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[199,280,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Thorax</emphasis>
. FW length: 
<quantity box="[431,555,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="82.0" valueMax="89.0" valueMin="75.0">75–89 mm</quantity>
, width: 
<quantity box="[647,769,547,573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="32.0" valueMax="34.0" valueMin="30.0">30–34 mm</quantity>
(ratio ~2.5), wingspan: 
<quantity box="[1043,1196,546,573]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="165.0" valueMax="180.0" valueMin="150.0">150–180 mm</quantity>
. DFW ground colour light brown to yellowish-brown; U-band indistinct, yellow-brown; stigma absent. DHW with apical area concolorous with DFW.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,464,655,681]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[199,305,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Abdomen</emphasis>
. As for the 
<specimenCount box="[436,460,655,681]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,563,691,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis box="[199,390,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Not dissected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,511,726,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[525,760,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis box="[525,760,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from single localities in the eastern Mexican states of 
<collectingRegion box="[251,327,763,789]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Puebla</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[381,480,763,789]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[496,580,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 48" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1727,1751]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,921,1704]" captionTargetId="figure-316@18.[151,1436,921,1704]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 48. Distribution of Schausiana spp. within southern North and Central America Eastern boundary of Guerrero terrane shown as blue dashed line." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4413530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4413530/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,467,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,467,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Host plants</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1312,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,1312,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Etymology</emphasis>
. It is likely the specific name comes from Greek mythology, son of Alcon from Athens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,871,897]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Druce" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[324,560,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phalerus">
<emphasis box="[324,560,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana phalerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from three specimens. Although none of the specimens were dissected, the wing ornamentation presents some features that clearly separate this species from 
<taxonomicName authority="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra, 2020" authorityName="Mielke &amp; Grehan &amp; Monzón-Sierra" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalciope" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana chalciope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[266,356,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,292,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">sp</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[305,349,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see diagnosis). The presence of specialized scales on the FW of both 
<specimenCount box="[1133,1154,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1206,1227,943,969]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
places this species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viette" authorityYear="1949" box="[180,309,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Schausiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[180,309,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Schausiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
